On the other hand, Sanofi, a major player in the antiplatelet drugs market, boasts a diverse portfolio that includes well-known products such as Aspirin and Plavix. Sanofi's commitment to research and development has enabled the company to continuously introduce new and improved antiplatelet medications to address the evolving needs of patients suffering from cardiovascular diseases. The company's global reach and distribution networks have allowed its products to reach a wide consumer base, further solidifying its market position.

In addition to Bristol-Myers Squibb and Sanofi, other notable players in the antiplatelet drugs market include Pfizer, AstraZeneca, and Bayer AG. These companies have also made significant contributions to the market by developing innovative antiplatelet medications and expanding their presence in key regions worldwide. Pfizer, for instance, offers antiplatelet drugs like Effient (Prasugrel) and Aggrastat (Tirofiban), which have been widely used in clinical settings for the prevention of cardiovascular events. AstraZeneca's portfolio includes antiplatelet medications such as Brilinta (Ticagrelor), which has gained popularity for its efficacy in reducing the risk of heart attacks and strokes.

